fight 6. jobober soundly trounced by hg seemed to want to cast his rune over and over again. didnt bother to rune and didnt seem really interested in meleeing him down. <br>
<br>
the score. HG 3 Pet 3. <br>
<br>
conclusion this pet sucks. plain and simple. pre 50 we had 4 useable pets. earth for keeping something in one place. water for good damage in groups or solo. air for stunning in groups or solo (didnt really tank well till 49). and fire for solo tanking against mobs that didnt hit rediculously hard. and the pets were well balanced between them, as far as pet duels went (except air attackin fire ).  well we still have earth water and air. but fire losing to a mob 10 lvls lower than it and 20 lvls lower than me is unexcuseable. seeing how 50% of our damage is our pets, and the pet is our only means of defense (besides running away and gate) the pet should at least be able to beat a monster 10 lvls lower than it. <br>
<br>
now i'll grant that this pet might be usefull in a group situation, if you can find the one that chainstuns, i havent been able to in the 30 or so times ive tried with 52, maybe thats just a trait of 58. will let ya know in a coupla days. <br>
but personally i'll take the tanking ability of air (pet mezz) and the reliable stun every 12 seconds or so from 53 air over the possiblility of this pet workin if i bother to cast enough of them to find the right spell line up. if verant really wanted us to be able to stun they could have given us the spell not this really lame pet. <br>
<br>
i also tried 52 fire vs every other pet from 56 to 44 and it lost to everything except rage of zomm ( go figure it can beat something with 100 hp) <br>
<br>
possible solutions: <br>
1. up the lvl of wizzy spells this thing casts so it is able to keep up damage wise with the other pets. fire had the least hp since its ds was awesome and it hit hard consitantly. lvl 45 wizzy should have a better spell lineup than lvl 20 spells. <br>
2. convert this pet to the old warrior model, give it back fireelementalaura. up melee damage to be in line with the rest of the vocarate pets. while your doing that change DDD(56) to this wizzy model and only give him stuns. <br>
3. add fire elemental aura to the existing pet rather than okeils radiation. ya know other than comedy value my pet running around casting a 2 point ds on itself and other pets is pointless. <br>
/sarcasm on<br>
4. convert the current pet to a cleric so it can at least heal itself while its getting its ass kicked by everything out there. <br>
5. ignore it and i just wont ever bother with fire pets again. <br>
/sarcasm off<br>
<br>
Tezron <br>
pissed off i had to run from an hg even if only long enough to summon a new pet. <br>
<br>
ps sorry I stopped on a tie. just didnt have the heart to waste any more malachite on this pet. i also realize i wasnt playing to the strenght of this pet since HG's cant be stunned. try it on the gnolls in jp (lvl 44ish) and it wont ever win. also i picked hg's since when i tried it against 51 earth it always seemed to get the earth pet to half health ( around 1500 hp) so it seemed like a reasonable test since most hg's have around 1500 hp. and thier 10 lvls lower on average than the pet. so spells should stick.<br>
